46:09.000 --> 46:15.000
The manager, who faithfully believed in the quality of the service of his company, was simply surprised by this.

46:15.000 --> 46:22.000
He kept asking the marketer why they were satisfied last year, and why these clients were not satisfied this year.

46:22.000 --> 46:36.000
This year we have improved our service much more. We bought furniture, trained our employees, installed coffee machines, and hung beautiful paintings.

46:37.000 --> 46:55.000
When a marketing agency surveyed the dissatisfied clients, they found out that the clients were dissatisfied with the service of the bank only because Nordstrom opened in Seattle.

46:55.000 --> 47:01.000
Nordstrom is a chain of shops that sells shoes and clothes.

47:01.000 --> 47:10.000
The manager could not understand what Nordstrom had to do with it when the marketing agency brought this information to them.

47:11.000 --> 47:32.000
If I come to a bank, I compare your service with the places where I was, the hotels where I was, the shops where I go to buy clothes, or the restaurants where I have dinner.

47:32.000 --> 47:46.000
If we are engaged in business services, we often have to do our service no worse than the service of the companies that our clients visit.

47:46.000 --> 47:53.000
You probably know this slide, I just wanted to comment on it.

47:53.000 --> 47:57.000
There are three stages of product or service development.

47:57.000 --> 48:04.000
1. Acceptable product. What does this mean? Our product must have minimum acceptable standards.

48:04.000 --> 48:12.000
This was observed in Russia, for example, in the late 80s and 90s. What did this mean?

48:12.000 --> 48:25.000
You only had to bring this product, and the hunger that the economy and consumers experienced was enough to grab this product, regardless of what quality you offer or what service you demonstrate.

48:25.000 --> 48:29.000
2. Acceptable product. This is the stage of product development.

48:29.000 --> 48:37.000
For example, in America, the times have changed from the early 1900s to the 1930s.

48:37.000 --> 48:43.000
Ford was able to produce one car model, and this was enough for customers to buy it.

48:43.000 --> 48:49.000
It was important for consumers to have a product of their own, and to be able to buy a cheap black car.

48:49.000 --> 49:00.000
But the competition grew and the market became what is called an acceptable product.

49:00.000 --> 49:06.000
The West has experienced this for decades, and Russia has quickly come to this.

49:06.000 --> 49:09.000
What is an acceptable product? It is a response to the needs of the consumer.

49:09.000 --> 49:18.000
Today, many companies face the problem of wanting to understand what the consumer wants, and to build a service or product to meet their needs.

49:18.000 --> 49:26.000
This is where the mass marketing research comes from, and the demand for marketing activities.

49:27.000 --> 49:32.000
The point is to understand what else the customer needs to buy.

49:32.000 --> 49:40.000
But the most surprising thing is that Russia and the rest of the world are entering the third stage of product development, which is called an acceptable product.

49:40.000 --> 49:47.000
What does this mean? It doesn't matter how you cut, it doesn't matter how you serve the customer.

49:47.000 --> 49:49.000
It is important to surprise them.

49:50.000 --> 49:55.000
You can't do better in your restaurant than in a competitor's restaurant.

49:55.000 --> 50:00.000
Very often you don't have enough money for this, so try to do it differently.

50:00.000 --> 50:09.000
Service is the area where real wars for differentiation begin.

50:09.000 --> 50:14.000
The conclusion is not to think about how to do something better, but to think about how to do it differently.

50:14.000 --> 50:20.000
This is the area that created the school called the Blue Kenan strategy.

50:20.000 --> 50:25.000
Do it differently, and only then will you find a new niche and be able to make money.

50:25.000 --> 50:33.000
Don't repeat the competitor. You didn't have time, you were late. You need to do something differently.

50:33.000 --> 50:50.000
